Dog's Name: Pup Daryl

Estimated Breed : Boxer Mix

Approximate Age: 6 months

Approximate Weight: approx. 39 lbs

Currently Living at: Boarding

Adoption Fee: $375

DOG'S DESCRIPTION

Pup Daryl is a sweet boxer mix hoping there is a family out there that will fall in love with him. He is very friendly, and still very much a puppy and will need room to run and play to get A LOT of exercise and training. Will you give Daryl a loving home?

Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.

Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.

Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org

Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!

For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.

animal.description:
**Hello!Camel is currently living in a foster home. If youd like to schedule a time to meet her please contact Waysides Adoption Center at 816-986-4426. Thank you!**
Hi there, Im Camel! I love you. I already know this because Ive never met a single person that I didnt love. Thats my gift to you, and besides, I believe that life is so much sweeter when you get to share it with the person you love. Im quiet and gentle and cuddly and typically just a little on the lazy side, as I search for the perfect soft spot to take a nap. And wait until you see me carry my favorite stuffy toys around the house. They make me happy. Anyway though, Im getting ahead of myself.
Im a darling, 7-year-old, 42-pound sweetheart, with an expressive face that will melt your heart and a delightful, easygoing, unassuming personality. And Im already mostly housebroken, as long as I get out on a regular schedule. I came to Wayside last summer, when my previous shelter was in the path of a hurricane. It ended up being the best thing for me, because I was able to get much needed vet care as well as extra TLC from the Wayside staff. Im currently staying in a foster home as I rest and recuperate and to give me a break from shelter life. Foster Mom and I have so much fun together, living the simple life and savoring each day. Ive never been happier in my whole life!
Ive had my fair share of health issues, but I never complain or feel sorry for myself. I came to Wayside with a bad case of heartworm disease, which has been treated, but it had already somewhat damaged my lungs and heart, causing me to tire easily. I also had masses removed from my chest area and I may have to have more surgeries for this in the future. Ive had a hard life and sometimes I just feel tired. But I never lose my zest for life! Im happy and I find that each new day is a reason to celebrate. Im looking for an adopter who will be there for me and make sure I have regular veterinary care. I have so much love to offer and living left to do! I just need your help with that. Please dont pass me by just because I need a little extra care.
Im perfect in the house! Foster Mom says Im the sweetest dog shes ever fostered. I like to snuggle and cuddle on the couch with an occasional play session mixed in for fun. Im quiet and calm and I dont bother a thing. Well, I do like to check out what youre having to eat though. Im not aggressive around food at all, but I like to snag a taste when I can. After all, isnt food meant to be shared with those you love? Ha! I just know from my past that its important to eat when you have the chance. I listen well and Im eager to please. Now that Ive discovered this little luxury called furniture, I cant get enough. I hope youll allow me to lounge on the couch or curl up in a chair. I love to be comfortable and, well, I deserve it!
Id love a quiet, calm, slow lifestyle where I can live my life in peace. I get easily tired, so I prefer not to have lots of stairs to climb. And I need a home without other animals. Im not typically reactive when I see other dogs at a distance during a walk, but I cant live with them, and Im not the sort of dog that you can take to a dog park or doggie daycare. I just need to keep my distance. I promise you Ill give you so much love that Ill be enough for you though! Mostly, I just want to be around my people, soaking up all the love you will give me. And Ill give it right back to you!
Life can be so hard, especially when youre all alone. And you do the best you can with what you have, but sometimes it takes someone special to step into your life and make all the difference. Ive had that now and I feel the love. Im just a sweet and simple dog looking for you to come into my life and never leave.
Love, Camel
P.S. I'm back at the shelter now, so please arrange to come on out to meet me! I'm waiting for you!
 ...

animal.description:
Hellooooo Kansas City! Im Marley.
I feel so flattered that you paused to let me tell you about myself. I am two years old and 65 pounds of pure sweetness. I have come such a long way in the past two months that Ive been at Wayside. A really nice officer found me roaming the streets alone and could tell I needed a warm place to lay my head and nice people to help me be my best self and that Wayside would be that place. He definitely was right about that!
Because of my rough start to life, I can be pretty nervous but settle in quickly once Ive had some time to get acclimated to my new environment. Ive never had toys of my own or people to give me treats so I havent quite figured out how fun those things can be and dont seem to show much interest. I have heard my two-legged friends here at Wayside talk about how amazing squeakies, plushies, kongs, and treats are so Im excited to have some of my own in my future home! Since I can be a little nervous, I will need to go to a home with kids 6 and up. Sometimes younger kids quick movements can startle me so I just want to make sure my new family can be as relaxed as me at home!
Since Ive been at Wayside for over two months now, Ive gotten to participate in Waysides Field Trip program. Its been AMAZING! Two really nice volunteers have taken me to places like Sonic, Burger King, the agility park (and regular park), and the Lowes parking lot. I did great at all of these places and loved getting to smell all the smells and eating all the yummy treats. I totally get why humans like fast food so much! I didnt mind the car but would get nervous sometimes its so hard not to when things are zooming by you so fast! Speaking of zooming, at the agility park I loved zooming around all the open space! I went through the tunnel and showed the volunteer how I already know some tricks like sit, down, and shake! I also loved sniffing out snacks in the grass my nose is my favorite if you couldnt tell! I also got to be an office foster. This means I got to hang out all day in someones cozy office instead of in my kennel. I greeted everyone who came into the office so nicely and always put my head in perfect position for a good scratch! My friend whose office I hung out in realized that once you are in my inner circle, I have so much love to give and can be so fun!
I know my photos make me all look so serious I havent quite learned how to smile. I know that smile will come once my forever family finds me and is ready to share all their love with me, the way I am ready to share my love with them. I hope youll come meet me and make me part of your family very soon.
Lots of love,
Marley

animal.description:
Scroll through Pwags photos to see him in action!
Helloooooo Kansas City, Professor Wagglesworth here but my friends call me PWags for short! Cant wait to tell you a little (or a lot, really) about me. First off, I am 1.5 years old and a perfect size of 46 pounds. I have a real zest for life and have been working so hard at Wayside to be the best version of myself to make someone an amazing companion for life!
I just passed my 150th day at Wayside and am still waiting for my people to call Wayside, ask to meet me, and take me home. Even though Ive been here quite a long time, I know the best things in life (like finding my forever family) just take time. The kind people at Wayside remind me everyday that I am so special and will make someone so happy, its just a matter of those special people finding me! I recently got to spend one night in a potential foster home and it was so amazing to get a taste of what life will be like once I do find my family. All I wanted the entire time was to get nice belly and head scratches. I also just love to cuddle! I like to think Im really the perfect combination of fun and chill. I LOVE to play, especially with toys. I also am like a puppy in the sense that I love to chew on things so I hope my future family will get me a bone or two to work on theyre just so fun! I also have been doing some puzzles at Wayside which has been great. Sometimes the days can feel long, especially after all this time at the shelter, so its nice to get to do fun things like this to help pass the time.
Speaking of fun things I also got to be an Office Foster for a day! This means that I got to spend some time outside of my kennel at Wayside which was so relaxing for me! It also means that I would be a great co-worker for you if you work from home!! If you dont work from home, I dont seem to mind the kennel so I would be happy to wait patiently for you to get home so we can spend time together then instead!
My friends here at the shelter have noted that I am really the best version of myself when I am on a routine of some sort. I will need a family that is committed to positive reinforcement training since I am still working on being the best version of myself. I have done well during playdates with other dogs here at the shelter but sometimes can get so excited that my new friends dont have as much fun as me. I definitely am open to going to a home with another four-legged friend but will need to meet them before heading home to make sure we are a great fit for each other. In my foster home I did live with a cat and she didnt seem to bother me! I will also need to go to a home with kids over the age of 10 and will need to meet any other family members living in the home before we make things official! Since Ive spent so much time in shelters, I just want to make sure that when I go home that its for forever this time!
If you think that we could be a good match for each other, we should participate in Waysides Slumber Paw-ty program. This means that you could take me home for a week to see if we are BFF potential and Wayside would provide all the items you would need to care for me. Its really an awesome thing. I hope to meet you soon!
Tail wags and wet nose kisses,
PWags

animal.description:
Hi there, I'm Rey! Im friendly and athletic and curious and loads of fun. I have an independent streak, so I wont constantly bother you for attention. But Im always game to exercise or hang out or have a little fun together. If youre familiar with and a fan of my breed, you will love me, because Im a typical Akitaa silly and affectionate soul who thrives on human companionship and the love of family.
Im a gorgeous, 5 year old, 56-pound sweetheart with an adorable, expressive face and an enthusiastic, spunky personality. I am truly beautiful both inside and out. And I think I may be already kennel trained, because I keep my area at Wayside clean and I know to go to the bathroom when I get outside. I came to Wayside as a transfer from a shelter in Louisiana when they were short on space. Im doing great here and Ive made lots of wonderful friends, but I have to admit that Im so tired of being homeless. Its time for me to find my family, so I hope youll come out to meet me and give me a chance to show you what a good dog I am.
Ive recently enrolled in a training program here at Wayside where Im learning basic commands and manners. I have so much fun working with my training partner! Im thriving with the extra attention and focus. Im smart and I love to learn, so I hope you continue to teach me throughout my life. I will do best with a patient and consistent family who will praise me when Im a good girl. I already know how to sit for my treats and I promise to take them gently from your hand. I love to play with my toys! They make me happy. I cant wait to spend my days with you, making you proud to have me as your dog.
Besides training and mental stimulation in my life, I will need regular daily exercise to help me stay happy, healthy, and calm. I like to keep both my mind and body busy. I am a strong, athletic dog and Im still working on my leash skills. I hope you can help me with that because I love going for walks or runs with you. I like to sniff and explore during my walks, curious of all that nature has to offer. I can climb a fence, so, if I have a fence in my new home, Ill need it to be at least 6 feet tall. Even then, I will need you to supervise me when Im outside to make sure I stay safe and secure. I can be picky about my dog friends and I do best with playful yet tolerant dogs. If you have another, I will need to meet them before we go home together, to make sure were a good match. I need a home without cats or small, furry animals because I like to chase them. I also need a home with kids over the age of at least 10. Im strong and still learning not to jump on people. Ive already made tons of progress during my stay at Wayside and I anticipate continuing to get better and better with time and training. 
Family is everything to me. Its all I think about. I cant wait to share my life with you and bring a little sunshine and fun into your world. I cant wait to be your dog.
Love,Rey

animal.description:
Hi there, Im Brodie!Im a friendly, goofy, happy dog who loves life. I believe that every single day is a reason to celebrate, no matter what circumstance it holds. I may not have had the ideal puppyhood, but today is a new day and I intend to savor it. Id love to share my zest for life with you!
Im a handsome, 1 year old, 49-pound sweetheart, with beautiful brindle fur, a bright smile, and an enthusiastic, delightful personality. I cant wait to make you laugh with my silly antics. I came to Wayside after I was rescued by the ASPCA. I was so happy to be here that I found myself jumping on everyone in pure joy to show my exuberance! Ha! Since that first day, Ive learned so much and Ive made great strides. I graduated from Waysides Peace Academy, which helps high energy dogs like me learn focus and manners. Ive been working really hard to learn appropriate behavior while still maintaining my charming love for life. Im so ready for my new life with you to begin! Im tired of being homeless.
After I graduated from the Peace Academy, I enrolled in the next level of training at Wayside. I am a superstar and one smart cookie who picks up on things very quickly. Nothing makes me happier than getting love and attention from my favorite people, so training sessions are my favorite time of the day. Ive already learned all sorts of commands as well as leash skills and basic manners. I love to make you proud of me and I try my best every day to learn something new.
Now that Ive been around awhile, I get chosen to go on field trips with the volunteers! Its an incredible time because it gives me a break from the shelter and teaches me about life on the outside. Everything is new to me and I love it all! Im getting used to the car rides and I find them quite enjoyable. I love to go walking or hiking in the local parks. And of course, a picnic is in order. I also enjoy hanging out and exploring at Petco, where Im friendly to everyone I meet. I like to pick out a special toy to take back to the shelter with me. I do love my toys! My only complaint is that I dont want these fun outings to end. I wish they could last forever! My friends reassure me that every day will be like one big, fun field trip once Im adopted. I cant wait!
Im looking for a home and family that will continue my training and provide me with extra exercise to help me stay happy, healthy, and calm. I will thrive in a patient, positive, and consistent environment. Please praise me when Im a good boy so that I can learn what you expect from me. Im super sweet and I love to spend time with my people. Daily exercise is important to me and Im a great partner if you feel like walking or running or hiking. My leash skills are phenomenalI wait patiently to be leashed up and then I walk right by your side, frequently looking to you for direction during our entire walk. I hope to have a fenced yard at my new home as well, for extra playtime. Im an expert at the game of fetch!
I was never socialized much with other dogs in my past, but Ive been working on that during my time at Wayside. I can be picky with other dogs, but Ive made some great friends who also have a high energy play style, and we love to run and play together. If you have another dog, I will need to meet them before we go home together, to make sure were a good fit for each other. And Im looking for a home with kids over the age of at least 6. The Wayside staff is setting me up for success by helping to find the best match for me. I like that.
Life isnt meant to be spent alone; I can attest to that. I long to be part of a family. I will be there for you no matter what life holdsmaking you smile, bringing comfort, helping you stay in shape. I promise to bring a little sunshine and fun into your life every single day. Please just give me a chance to shine!
Love, Brodie

animal.description:
**Check out Angelos video by scrolling through his photos!**
Hi there, Im Angelo! Im a happy, affectionate boy who loves to be with my people. Ill greet you each day with the most beautiful smile and a joyous wag of my tail, just to show you how much you mean to me. Ive never had much in life, so I savor and appreciate every bit of good that comes my way. I cant wait to be your loyal companion and best buddy.
Im a handsome and strong, 4 year old, 58-pound sweetheart with a gentle spirit and soulful eyes to go along with my delightful personality. And Im already housebroken! Please stay patient with me though when we get home, because Ive been living at the shelter for a while now and its hard to keep up my routine here. I promise to try my best to follow all the rules of my new home. I came to Wayside as a transfer from another shelter. Even though its not quite a real home, I understand that this is just another stop on my journey, so Im making the most of it. Ive had some of the best days of my life at Wayside, and everything Ive experienced has helped to prepare me for my new home with you. But Im tired of being homeless and life in a shelter can be stressful. So, I hope you come for me soon!
Ive made lots of new friends and the volunteers think Im pretty special! In fact, my best friend comes in every Monday to take me for a field trip, giving me a break from shelter life. I find that the most important things in life sometimes leave us without adequate words, and this is one of those occasions. When youve lived in a shelter for so long, its hard to describe the feeling of a few hours of freedom with your friend. But Ill try. I love going for car rides and Im an excellent rider, sometimes resting my head on your shoulder, just to feel the connection. My friend and I have a routine. We go to the McDonalds drive through for a treat and then share it during a picnic at the park. I love to go for walks and meet people along the way. Next stop is Petco, where I greet all the employees and pick out a new toy. Lowes is another favorite stop. All the employees are so happy to see my wagging tail and big smile. Im a regular there and I savor the love and attention. Monday is my favorite day of the week!
I was recently chosen for a slumber pawty by a potential adopter. It didnt end up working out for me, because I didnt get along with the resident cat, but I had such an excellent time! I got to sleep in the bed at nightbest sleep Ive had in ages! I didnt have any accidents and I did just fine in my crate when no one was home. I loved running and playing in the fenced yard. Simply hanging out with the family was my favorite thing to do. I just loved that feeling of belonging that comes with being a member of a family. They said I was a great dog and such a nice friend.
Im currently enrolled in a weekly training class, which I love. Ive made excellent progress, learning basic commands and manners in a positive, structured, consistent environment. I have a strong will, so I need a family who can establish and maintain boundaries with me while providing me with mental and physical stimulation. Daily exercise helps me stay happy, healthy, and calm. Im a friendly and playful dog and I love to go for walks or play with my toys. Id love a home and family where I can be included in activities and fun. I prefer dogs that are my size or larger or I'll be happy as your only dog as well. If you do have another dog that is on the small side, please bring them out to Wayside to meet me to make sure were a good fit for each other. I do need a home without cats. And due to my size and strength, I will also need a home with kids over the age of 10. I really want this adoption to last forever, so lets make sure were a good match from the start!
Being homeless has taught me never to take things for granted. A simple car ride, a picnic, fresh air, someone to share my day with, attention from the people I lovethese are the things that make me happy. Now I want to share my life with you and be there for each other the way families do. I will be so proud to be your dog, every single day for the rest of my life!
Love, Angelo

animal.description:
Scroll through Dusk's photos to see him in action!
Hi there, Im Dusk! Im friendly and affectionate and playful and so much fun! Im smart too, and I love to learn. It might take me just a little extra time to warm up, but once we bond, I will be your best companion ever. I just need someone to believe in me and love me, so that we can do all the things that families do together and for each other. Im ready for the next chapter of my life to begin!
Im a handsome, 2-year-old, 50-pound sweetheart with gentle eyes and a happy, delightful personality. I love being around my people! And I think I might already be housebroken, because I keep my kennel clean and I know to go to the bathroom when I get outside. Please stay patient with me though, as I get used to my new routine with you. I came to Wayside when someone abandoned me on the property. I dont know why that happened, but I felt so alone and humiliated. When the staff welcomed me in, I was confused and afraid, but my sweet, affectionate personality started shining through when they offered me treats and gentle praise. That felt good!
I already know all sorts of commands that I cant wait to show you, including Sit, Down, Shake, High Five, and Touch. I hope you will continue to teach me throughout my life because I love to learn new things. If you stay patient with me and praise me when Im a good boy, Ill quickly learn what you expect from me and gain confidence at the same time. I love to play with my toys and especially balls! They make me happy. I wont bother you for constant attention, but when you call my name, Ill be there as fast as I can! I like to spend time with you and soak up the attention you give. I love tasty treats and I take them gently from your hand. Im just an all-around nice dog.
Im an athletic guy and I love to play and act silly. I never turn down a fun game of fetch and Im an expert at it! I also enjoy going for a daily walk. I hope youll let me go at my own pace when we get home. I like to take things slowly and get comfortable with my environment in my own time. I will thrive in a calm, quiet, positive, consistent home where I know what to expect. Im looking for a home without a lot of commotion and I like my space, so Ill need a home with kids over the age of at least 6. And I need to be your only dog, but I promise to give you so much love that Ill be enough. 
Im so excited about what my future holds! Its been quite a journey for me and it hasnt always been easy, but I feel in my bones that this is where I need to be in order for you to find me. I cant wait to share my life with you and be your best friend.
Love, Dusk

animal.description:
Please call the shelter at (706) 795-2868 to schedule a meet and greet.

Madison Oglethorpe Animal Shelter is a non-profit shelter serving over 720 square miles. We are open intake, meaning we can not turn away animals from either county we serve. Our shelter intakes double or triple it's capacity every month so it is essential we place animals quickly into adoptive homes. Since so many animals enter the shelter we often don't have enough volunteers to write an individual bio for each. Please feel free to call the shelter Wednesday-Sunday to inquire about the animal you are interested in. 706-795-2868.

Viewing and adoption hours at our shelter are Wednesday through Sunday from 12 PM to 5 PM. 
All adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, flea treatment, deworming, and spay or neuter, microchip, and adoption packet. 
Fees:
Dogs over 4 months old: $100
Puppies under 4 months: $125. 
Cats and Kittens are $75 ($65 without microchip). 

For your convenience you can fill out an adoption application for any of our current residents at www.moaspets.com. Join us on Facebook at
https://www.facebook.com/moaspets. It's a great way to stay up to the minute on the furry 4 legged friends we have looking for a loving forever home. 
We are located at:
1888 Colbert Danielsville Rd 
Danielsville, GA 30633 
706-795-2868

NOTE: Our adoptions are first come first served, simply filling out an application does not mean the animal will be held for you, you must come meet the animal in person in order to be considered for adoption.
If you rent you must bring your lease or a letter from your landlord stating you may adopt.

animal.description:
Coyote found herself homeless and trapped inside an overcrowded animal shelter. She had a bad skin infection and no fur and was no far from being euthanized before we stepped in and saved her. She went into a foster home who cared for her skin problem and now look at her. She's got such beautiful marble colored markings. She's a possible great pry or shepherd mix about 3 years old and just a great gal. She's gotten some training and is crate trained. She gets along with all dogs and humans but has not been cat tested. She has average energy and moderate shedding. 

She is currently in Fort Worth, TX but will making the trek to Olympia, WA scheduled to arrive on Saturday Jan 23rd IF she is pre-adopted meaning you need to get your app in, approved and pay the adoption fee to secure her.  Her adoption fee is $450 which covers her spay, vaccinations, HW testing, chipping, health certificate and transport fees. All our dogs come with a 30 day, money back, trial period to make sure they are the right fit in your environment. Tall Tails Rescue has a commitment to these dogs for their lifetime and we hope you do too! If you are thinking of adopting any of our dogs contact us today! Please click here or copy and paste the link here to fill out the application to get started: https://form.jotform.com/PNWdogs/ttrt-pnw-ap

animal.description:
Milli was a stray that was taken in at an "owner surrender" event up in Naytahwaush, MN. She came to us in season and we were unsure if she was expecting but after about 6 weeks it was evident and thus she gave birth in rescue to an adorable litter of health puppies. Milli is figured to be primarily a Shepherd x Lab cross with possibly a little bit of pittie because of her weak brindling coloration but she does not show any other feature of pitbull (this is only a guess). Milli is a healthy 55# girl that is patiently waiting to be spayed now that her puppies have been weaned from her. 
Milli is vaccinated, dewormed, will be chipped prior to adoption, HWT - negative, and awaiting spay. If Milli is adopted prior to her spay she will have to require a spay/neuter contract to be signed. 
Milli has been around various animals in her foster home and she has shown soe prey instincts towards cats and she is slightly aggressive with dogs smaller than her, she has been doing well with the dogs that are 70# or larger. Milli is quiet natured and submissive with people. She is an attention hog and loves hugs, belly rubs and good ear scratches. She will require a fenced yard as she does want to run off. She is not much for playing with toys but will chew on antlers, buffalo horns, and nylabones. She does know some obedience skills like sit and down (to lay down) and off.

animal.description:
***Thank you for your interest in Magnificent Mutts and Meows. We hope everyone is saying safe during this challenging time. Due to the current regulations set forth by Governor Pritzker on group gatherings we will not be having adoption events until further notice. As an all foster based rescue this means that all meets will be by appointment only. Your whole family must be available to attend the meet as there will be no second meets scheduled to help limit contact between our team and the public. To help streamline the process please make sure your current pets are up to date, you have landlord/HOA approval, and that you are prepared to take the dog home with you immediately before submitting an application. Thank you & Please stay safe!***

Network to us from a rescue partner in the south Lelo just arrived. Approximately 2 years old and 52 lbs this gal is as sweet as they come.
Lelo is a super curious, sweet and docile young pup. She is well behaved, and house-trained. She lo

ves pets and kisses and keeps a constant eye on her people. She understand the commands to sit and come, but needs to learn to not jump up when she gets overly excited. She takes treats with a gentle mouth and sleeps well in her crate. She'll be a great dog for an active person or family.

Check back for more information and possible restrictions once he fully settles into foster care.

If you are interested in adoption, please complete the Application to Adopt which you can find on our website (
www.magnificentmutts.org
) No phone calls please. Emails only.

Adoption Donation $300 (cash only)

Please visit www.magnificentmutts.org for the online dog or cat application.

Adoption Fees*

Adult cats starting at $125, Kittens starting at $165.
Dogs/Puppies starting at $225 minimum
Prices subject to change, please contact for specific adoption donations.

animal.description:
Meet Freya! She is around 5 months old and 25 pounds (1/11).
 This AL beauty romped into her foster home like she had always lived there. She found the toys and made herself at home. She is happy to play by herself but does love other dogs. She is good at listening to social queues but can push her luck sometimes. 
 She loves her comfort either lying on the couch beside you or taking over the comfiest bed. She loves to romp in the snow. She walks well on a leash. She is fun and quirky e.g. she sploofs instead of lying down. She is just an all round lovely girl!

Interested in this sweet young dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

*Please note that all breeds noted are estimates or best guesses. We very rarely have information on our animals' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays*

animal.description:
Meet Hera! This beauty was found running the rough streets of the St. Roch area, dragging a leash behind her.  
Besides being stunning, Hera is SWEET, SWEET.  She’s around 54 lbs., two years old, spayed, heart worm negative, house trained, and kennel trained.  She gets along GREAT with dogs but has that typical high-octane pitty energy, so having another dog that would equal that would be best.  She loves people, and playing with toys is her favorite past time! Not sure about cats. This sweetheart is ready to bring love and adventure to your home.

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet our handsome boy, Cade!

Cade was found as a stray. When, after 2 months nobody claimed him, Diamonds stepped in to find him a new home.

Cade is currently living with his foster mom, who describes him as an overgrown lap dog. He absolutely loves to snuggle and wants to be wherever his person is. His current favorite place to be is snuggled up on his bed next to the fireplace.

Cade is fully housebroken and has absolutely no problem being left alone, however no crates please, this boy hates being contained. Cade loves chewing on his bones and is very good at knowing what is his to chew on and what is not. Cade also has had basic leash training and loves to go on long walks. He is extremely treat motivated and knows basic commands.

Cade's ideal home would be one that is quiet and structured. He is good with children, however, older/respectful children would be ideal as he can get a little overzealous when excited. A home without cats is a must. Cade is currently not dog friendly, however has shown promise that he eventually could be with the proper training and socialization. Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ THIS PROFILE AND THE REQUESTED CRITERIA BEFORE CALLING OR SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. THANKS FOR YOUR ATTENTION AND CONSIDERATION 

MEET GONZO!  He is so unique…but no blue fur or a long nose!  His right eye was recently enucleated, and it took him a bit to get used to it missing.  Gonzo is a character, and one of the most affectionate dogs we have ever had!  He is probably a Cockapoo, 3 yrs old, 15 lbs and full of cuddles and kisses.  He looked like Pic #4 when we got him…so  sad and forlorn!

But look at him now!!  He looks like a puppy and acts like a puppy!  He is soooooo loveable.  He is good with everyone.  When he arrived, he did a little submissive peeing…but that has improved 90%.  He was a little frightened and needed to settle down.  But…you have to be prepared — just know he grows out of it!  Gonzo wants to engage with YOU, so he would not be good in a home where someone else cares for him.  He needs to bond and when he does, he’s really a Velcro dog who loves his toys (see the video), loves to give kisses, plays fetch the ball, would love older kids (8+) and LOVES YOU!  He is a little socially awkward in crowds or where there are loud noises…he likes other dogs, but not as much as he likes people.  We have seen him blossom but know he has more blossoming to go!  Gonzo doesn’t have separation anxiety, he just gets sad when he is alone.  He isn’t a barker, he’s a lover not a fighter!  We don’t think he’s a daredevil like his namesake….but who knows what lies ahead!  He will need training and attention…but you can’t go wrong with this GONZO MAN!!

Our website is updated daily. Please do not apply for this dog unless your home fits the specified criteria. All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, groomed, vet checked, dewormed, deflea'd and come with a leash, collar and ID If you are interested in adopting this dog from Lhasa Happy Homes, please complete the adoption application via the link below: Adoption (Online) Application: https://lhasahappyhomes.org/adoptions/adoption-application/. We will contact you once it has been reviewed. 

During the COVID-19 quarantine, Lhasa Happy Homes will NOT be holding weekly adoption events. We will set up individual meet & greets with APPROVED applicants once they have submitted a video tour of their home. 

You can check our Events Calendar at http://www.lhasahappyhomes.org/HLM_Custom_Calendar.aspx.

Thanks for thinking rescue and adoption…and for considering saving a life. It will be the best gift you ever give yourself or your family.

animal.description:
Barks and Meows Rescue introduces Precious. She is a Romanian Mioritic Sheepdog that may have some Caucasian Shepherd in her as both breeds were being bred there. She was surrendered to our rescue at 8 months of age, having come from a Backyard Breeder who was closing down. She has long fur which will require professional grooming 4 times a year. Precious shows all the wonderful traits of the Romanian Mioritic Sheepdog. She is very loving with the family in her foster home and enjoys meeting new people. This breed is a guardian breed so would protect the family if needed. Continuing socialization is the key to ensuring she remains always an outgoing, fun dog to be around. Precious is wonderful with the three children in the home, ages 8-14. She plays with the other two male dogs and definitely loves the cooler weather and snow. They are not known for huge appetites so she is eating 2 cups of food, twice daily. Precious is eating large breed puppy food and will remain on it until she is 18 months of age. She is only halfway through her growing stage and currently weighs about 82 pounds. She has long legs and gigantic paws. Her family has taught her to walk on a leash, which was a huge task in itself. She takes her trust of other people from her family members. If they like the person, she will as well. She has a deep bark, only using it if need be. This breed is not a yappy one. She usually sleeps on the couch and sometimes beside the bed. They get warm very easily so enjoy laying on a cold floor in the warmer months. She did meet a cat outside of the cage at PetValue and didn't even look at it. Precious loves all dogs including puppies. She has lived amongst multiple dogs her entire life, so a second large socialized canine will be mandatory in her new home. She has gone for a groom and did very well but laid down in the tub. She does well in the car ride now that she can walk on a lead. She does hate the body harness so she is walked on a Martindale collar. The ideal home for Precious is one where the family is patient with her as she came to us quite feral. She has learned to trust her family members, so kindness, patience, and consistency are key. She is used to the children in the home, who are very dog savvy, working with her on tricks, leash training, etc. We would like to see her in a home with children 8 years up who all have guardian breed experience. She really doesn't realize how big she is and is a giant lap dog. She has had issues with some female dogs in the past so best suited as an only dog. Precious is spayed, up to date with vaccines, and dewormed. A fully fenced yard, children 8 years plus, and a Veterinarian History of Compliance are mandatory to apply for Precious.
Visit barksandmeows.ca for an online application. Available to Ontario Residents only!!!

***ADOPTION PENDING***

PLEASE READ THIS PROFILE AND THE REQUESTED CRITERIA BEFORE CALLING OR SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. THANKS FOR YOUR ATTENTION AND CONSIDERATION 

THIS IS SASHA…a zaftig, tan/white, 23.5 lbs (yes, she’s on a diet) Lhasa Apso…and she’s a doll!!  Sasha came from a senior home where she was very loved but spoiled.  Because of health reasons (mom) they had to give her up.  Sasha was groomed monthly, vetted properly, very loved but she wasn’t walked or fed on a schedule.  So, she had gained a few “Covid” pounds!  She loves treats but is a bit picky in the food department — but she is learning. 

She loves to go for walks at a brisk pace now!  For this reason, she wold not be good in a senior home.  She needs several walks daily and she’s pretty good.  She wakes up at 7:30am every morning and asks to go out!  She will have an accident here and there (usually on a pp pad)…but she is doing well.  We taught her how to walk up and down the stairs and she learned in two days! 

We were told that Sasha has a couple of issues, she’s a Lhasa after all!  We have not seen them yet, but she will let you know if she doesn’t like something.  SHE IS NOT AGGRESSIVE.  She can be food possessive if you drop food on the floor and she wants it — just don’t try to take it out of her mouth!  She is great with other dogs — she’ll even let them eat out of her bowl and she loves to play with them.  She won’t let you clean her behind, so don’t try (unless you are tricky and fast)!   Sasha has blossomed in her foster home and shown that she definitely wants another small, active dog as her companion; NO cats and she doesn’t like being left alone all day.  That being said, she can be independent in the house.   She is a wonderful companion and ultimately will give you lots of kisses!  Loves toys!!  No kids, because of her food issues, and it would be best for her to live in a house because she is a great watch dog and will bark if she hears noises.  Sasha is a wonderful dog but she needs alpha owners who will take charge of her.  Otherwise, she will take charge of you!  Does Sasha sound like a dog you could love?  WE DO!!!

animal.description:
Meet Echo! 

After being dumped in the middle of the country, Echo found herself surrounded by cornfields all alone. Unfortunately we do not know how long she was there, but from her emaciated state we assume she had spent some time there. As you can imagine, Echo was absolutely petrified when she arrived to her foster home. Everything she had ever known had changed and her world had turned upside down. Echo was found with a harness on, and after several weeks in her foster home she finally felt safe. But it was clear that someone love Echo before... she knows several tricks and is already potty trained. 

Echo is a special girl who will need an owner who knows that sometimes the world is still scary for Echo. As many Great Danes are, Echo is very sensitive and her spirit is still rebuilding. She feels that she has to protect her food and her favorite things from other dogs when she first meets them, but with slow introductions Echo will stop protecting these things. This behavior is common with dogs who have been neglected. Echo is currently living with several other dogs and is doing well with them. 

Once Echo trusts you, she will love you forever. She is goofy, playful, and is all Dane! She loves to chew on her favorite benebone, but is afraid of squeaky toys. She loves to run around the yard, but she’s still too afraid to go on walks. 

Echo needs someone to take the time to build trust. She needs someone who will move slow. She needs someone to show her that life is good again, and that she’s going to be okay. 

Echo is around a year old. She is approximately 90lbs and is expected to grow a bit more. She came to us thin and will need time to gain the weight she needs. She is spayed, vaccinated, heartworm tested, microchipped, dewormed, current on flea and heartworm prevention, and has had a gastropexy done. Echos adoption fee is $425. 

REQUIREMENTS
- secure fully fenced yard. 
- no children 
-a low traffic home without frequent visitors 
-previous experience with owning a large breed dog, or ability to demonstrate research done on owning a large breed dog. 
- a patient owner who will make sure introductions to other dogs is slow. 

If you are interested in learning more about Echo, apply today at farfetcheddogrescue.org

If you are looking to help the littlest of pups - Ellie Mae is a 4 lb long-haired Chi/Pomeranian mix that needs all the help and love she can get!  Ellie Mae is looking at some difficult months ahead while we find out if her heart with a grade 4 murmur can withstand some mammary tumor removals.  So if you have either the financial ability to help or the heart to adopt this tiny peanut for as long as she has - please reach out!

Ellie Mae is currently in a foster home and spends her days with her furr-foster brothers/sisters and this pint-size Alpha dog stands on her own!  She is a sweet girl and would love nothing more than a fuzzy bed right beside you for the rest of her days.

If you are interested in adopting, please reach out to adoptsch@gmail.com and ask for an application.  After receipt, we can arrange a meet and greet with Ellie Mae.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Luna and I am at the Santa Maria Campus. I am a 4 year-old, female, German Shepherd mix who is eager for a new home!

I am serene and very affectionate, and enjoy gentle walks and soothing talks!

My ideal home would be as tranquil as I am. I can be upset by too much noise and activity. If we can match up in energy levels and style, you'll have a loyal friend for life.

You would love to add me to your family if you enjoy spending quiet and reflective time with your dog, and enjoy bonding as deeply as I do.

Ready to adopt or want to hear more about me? The shelter is open by appointment seven days a week! Just email adopt@sbhumanesociety.org to make an appointment today!

When you take your new pet home, he or she will have been spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations, provided with a permanent microchip identification and a certificate for a free veterinary exam. Our partners at Purina brand dog and cat food also provide food to get you home. 

Transfer of animals may be available between our Santa Maria and Santa Barbara Campuses. If an animal you would like to meet is at the campus further away from you, just let us know when you email, and we will be in touch with you if a transfer is available. Our adoption fees help support our community programs and the next animal who needs our help!

animal.description:
Where are my GSD lovers?!
Meet Lobo, a very sweet German Shepard mix with the floppiest ears from MDAS that had been decompressing in his foster home and doing great! MDAS estimated he was 6 years old, but or vet thinks he's closer to eight years old; even though he's 70lb, he's got a smaller build to the average GSD. And he may be a senior, but this dog's got game - Lobo LOVES to play with tennis balls and can't wait to catch them in the air or chase them across the room!
Lobo is healthy, up to date on vaccines, has a microchip, neutered, and ready for his forever home! He is potty trained and just wants to stick to your side and follow you like a shadow. Even though he loves to play with his tennis balls, he enjoys taking it easy and chilling with you on the couch to watch Netflix too.
Like most dogs, he has a warm up period... But once he gets used to you, he's a total velcro dog and will stick to you like glue! We think his ideal home would be as a solo dog to get all the attention and love, please no cats or small animals (he thinks they are fun to chase). Currently in his foster home he lives with older kids and doing great playing with them.
If you think your home would be a good fit for Lobo, please complete an adoption application.

animal.description:
Chloe and Jorge are the absolute sweetest! They are two peas in a pod

and looking for an adoptive home together!

They love to be petted and have small snuggle sessions. They will be your shadow everywhere you go too. Both are potty trained and walk well on leashes. Chloe and Jorge are very attached to each other, and get nervous if the other isn't around, but they love people company too. They do well with the small dog in their foster home, but bark at larger dogs in true chihuahua fashion. Chloe is the timid and the shy one, while Jorge is more jovial. They love to play with kids and would do well with older dog savy children. Belly rubs are the best and boy, do they LOVE belly rubs! Anyone who takes these two bonded sweethearts will be lucky and loved for a long time! Apply to adopt Chloe and Jorge today at www.underhoundrailroad.org.

Chloe and Jorge are currently being fostered in North Carolina and may transport to their adoptive home.

animal.description:
Welcome Lance to CCPAL Rescue.  He is a beautiful Shepherd/Lab dog weighing 40 lbs.  He is potty trained, smart and loyal.  He gets along great with the bigger dog in this home.    Here is one bossy Chi that he doesn’t much like.  His best home is either only dog or dog his size.  He would be fine with children and we always like 8 and older.  He is great with all people he has met and he gets to go to work with his mom to the grooming salon.  He is the shop favorite and very social.  He does not get along with cats so his home will need to be cat free.  He would do best with a fenced yard and would make a great companion for some active family.  He is smart and has a lot of the qualities of the Shepherd.  He is currently in Texas and can be adopted locally in Texas or we can work with one of the wonderful transporters to deliver him to Washington, Portland, Wisconsin, Minnesota, Vermont or all along the East Coast.  His adoption fee is 250 and transport is 185.  Rhode Island and Massachusetts are not states we adopt to because of the regulations imposed by these states. 

Contact Marlene at 210-867-1769 or email to ccpalinquiries@gmail.com if you have questions. Online applications at www.ccpal.info/ See his cute video!!

animal.description: **Gus will be available for adoption approximately 3-1-21 following heartworm treatment* Gus is loving every minute of his new life! He can't get enough of his toys and makes every moment of playtime count. He's such a happy-g0-lucky boy! Gus came to Dolly's Legacy after being confiscated by animal control in a small Missouri town due to neglect. He had been living outdoors and not receiving proper care. He is so grateful he's now a rescue dog! Gus is a male Hound/Lab mix who weighs 75 lbs and was born approximately 12-22-18. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, given flea/tick preventative, dewormed. Gus had life-saving treatment for heartworm disease. He will need to remain on heartworm preventative for life, as is recommended for ALL dogs, and retested in 6 months to ensure he is heartworm free. Adoption fee is $400 to help offset the many expenses we have for vetting costs. We rely strictly on adoption fees and donations to continue to save the lives of orphaned & abandoned pets; 100% goes towards their care. If interested in adopting one of our available dogs or puppies, please complete an online adoption application at https://dollyslegacyanimalrescue.org/adopt/ You will be contacted by our adoption coordinator via email after your application has been reviewed & approved to schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
Fiona is a sweet shy girl, that came to us from a shelter in North Carolina.  She does want pets and attention, but she needs time to adjust to a new home. A friendly playful dog really helps with that.. and she has a few to chose from in her foster home.

Because she is shy, she may easily be scared in a busy household and would do best in a home with older children.  Fiona 's new family should have a physical fenced yard to ensure that she gets enough exercise and potty breaks, as her leash skills are lacking some. 



If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org 

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

animal.description:
Ingrid is a 1.5 year old energetic mixed breed dog. She looks like she has some Dutch Shepherd mixed.

She would be a good only dog. Calm in her pen. Crate trained, No potty accidents Inside.  Fine in yard with no leash  just wants to sit and be with her foster family.  Other dogs should be ok, with slow introductions. She has a strong play style that other dogs need to get used to first.

She is currently still in her foster home in North Carolina. We are looking for a foster home  here in Maryland or the potential of a foster to adopt home to bring her here. From her NC foster:

From being found as a stray and living in a cement shelter kennel for 6 months to cuddling with her foster sisters and napping on the sofa.
Ingrid is doing fabulous with routine. While she is still a bit overpowering in play with my girls, she quiets down with instruction.
Ingrid learned how to use the dog door and goes in and out when she needs.
She  still doesn't like to be left alone outside for long. She will come running to the door when she realizes nobody is outside with her.  I think she doesn't want to be "left behind." Ingrid shows no other separation anxiety- she is perfect in her pen overnight and when we leave the house.


If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org 

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies)  and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

We are working on leash  training and general life skills such as riding in cars and not jumping on people. River has spent time with kids and prefers children over 8 years old. 
The first year of life has not been easy for this amazing girl. 
River's dream family would be fairly calm with lots of time for snuggles. River has an impressive bark and is not an option for apartment living. A fully fenced back yard is required. NO ELECTRIC  FENCED yards will be approved. 
If you are serious about adopting River and meet these requirements,  please fill out the application at savealifepets.org/adopt.

animal.description:
Frances is a ten-year-old Chihuahua mix.  She weighs around 15 lbs. is spayed, and will be up to date on her shots as of 1/26.  A few weeks ago, she had a full blood panel, and her teeth cleaned.  She is a very healthy girl.  She was given to us by a loving couple that had her since she was a puppy.  She slept in bed with them and was adored.  Unfortunately, this couple's two-year-old daughter was diagnosed with cancer, and their world fell apart.  They are spending so much time in and out of hospitals, Frances was not getting any attention.  She was depressed when she first came to our foster home.  She has holistic supplements she has been taking, and she is feeling more like herself.  If you are looking for a gentle, calm walking buddy, Frances is your gal. She literally lights up and does a happy dance when you say the word “walk.” Being the older and wise lady she is, she reminds you to pause now and then to look (or sniff in her case) around and be present. She is a very easy-going, calm dog with lots of love to give though she may need a bit of time and space initially to establish safety and trust. She needs someone who understands patience to help her navigate this confusing stage of changing homes. Once you gain her trust, her cuddly and affectionate self would come out (though infrequently at first) via a warm gaze, wanting to be in your proximity and asking to be held. If you are interested in meeting Frances, fill out our easy online application. 

http://www.angelsinfurdogrescue.com/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Have you met Macy?

Macy was relinquished to the San Diego Humane Society by her family, who said they couldn't prevent her from escaping their home, and she had separation anxiety. They also said Macy had lived with young children and a small dog and was good with both. She does great with all of our little dogs here at Frosted Faces, and she's a favorite hiking buddy of our volunteers
! Be sure to watch the cute videos of Macy hiking and showing off her "sit" and "spin". She's so cute! Macy is 12 years old and weighs 15 lbs.

Sweet Macy went on a two week Frosted Fling over the holidays, and she recently was scooped up to live in an awesome Foster home. We received a great update from her Foster Mom: "

Macy is settling in well in her foster home! We're still learning about her and letting her decompress, but I can confirm some of the things her previous Fling parents have noted:

-Macy is a sweet 12 year old terrier who doesn't look or act her age. She has very few teeth and is a little itchy but doesn't have any major medical issues. She'll make a wonderful companion, even for children and other dogs!

-She is potty trained! She hasn't asked to go out yet, but, with 3+ outings a day, she always does her business outside.

-She sleeps through the night in her crate or her own bed. Snuggles are for the couch.

- She is patient with our other foster Ida and shows no food guarding or aggression of any sort.

- She has great hearing and knows "sit", "spin", and "no". We're working on being better at "stay". She's very smart and definitely trainable. Very food motivated.

-She loves walks and jogs. She'll be a great hiker.

- She climbs stairs like a pro and can easily get on/off the bed or couch.

- She barks at the doorbell or if another dog barks at her. We live on the second floor and don't have any furniture under windows where she can watch pedestrians or squirrels, so she's been pretty quiet!

-She has some anxiety and is known to be a skilled escape artist.

So far we are handling her "flightiness" by making sure she is in a snug fitting harness and on leash when outside and that we are very careful coming and going. She hasn't darted but is interested in the door. Macy did very well on a visit to foster grandma's house, as well. We made sure all the doors were secure and had no issues. She was a very polite house guest. There

have been conflicting reports about Macy's separation anxiety. We haven't left her alone yet but will do so soon and report back."

Check back soon for the next update on Macy!

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption

fees, and we help with medical costs!

Apply to become family:
www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated 2/2

animal.description:
Adoption info can be found in the last paragraph of this pet's profile or by visiting this direct link:   https://www.dfwpuppatrol.com/info/adoption

Herbert is a sweet Great Pyrenees puppy.  He went to the vet with a few broken toes in September, 2020 and has had a very long road to recovery ever since, but is finally done with all that and ready to find his forever family.  Having to wear a cast and a cone never stopped him though!  He is such a sweet, loving pup. He loves to run around in the backyard playing and chasing all day as well as sunbathing too.  He is never ready to go inside (typical Pyr)! He can be a little shy with big dogs, even though he himself is a big dog......it just takes him a bit to warm up.  He loves playing with small dogs like his Pomeranian foster brother, but don’t worry he is oh so gentle. We are looking for a new forever home for him where there is another well matched companion dog for him.

Herbert can be a bit timid and shy at first when meeting new people.  He is also scared of loud noises and will find the smallest place possible to hide. Once he gets to know you he will absolutely adore you! Herbert is completely potty trained and crate trained too. He likes cuddles and laying in bed with his humans. He knows the commands “sit” and “paw” and is super treat motivated. He is very vocal and loves to talk back too. Herbert was born around the end of March, 2020 and currently weighs approximately 51 lbs.  Herbert's new home must be located in the immediate area of Dallas/Ft. Worth, TX.

If you are interested in adding this pup to your family, please click here (or copy and paste https://www.dfwpuppatrol.com/info/adoption into your browser) to view our adoption info and where you will find the link to fill out our online Pre-Adoption Application.  Any questions can be directed to us at info@dfwpuppatrol.com.  All of our adoptable pups have a minimum requested adoption fee of $250 + tax  (pups 6 months and older) and $350  + tax (pups under 6 months old), regardless of our expenses, and it includes vaccinations, spay/neuter, heartworm test for pups 8 months and older, heartworm treatment if tested positive, deworming and/or fecal test, parasite treatment if tested positive, microchipping, any immediate known health issues, and pups 3 months and older are kept current on monthly heartworm prevention.

WHAT'S NEXT?

If you would like to meet, foster or adopt this pet, please fill out our online FOSTER/ADOPTION APPLICATION which can be found in the main menu of our website or at the bottom of this page - simply copy and paste the link into your browser. EASY PEASY!

***

This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives.

Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. 

BY APPOINTMENT ONLY:  Meetings at our Adoption Center are by appointment only (no walk-ins).  An online adoption application is required and must be approved prior to meeting any animals.  Adoption appointments are set up by email by our Adoption Coordinator (no phone calls, please).  This process ensures our dedicated time to the animals in our care, as well as full attention to adopters at scheduled times.  

Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details.

To fill out an adoption application, go to:
https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

These pups are NOT in the shelter and you MUST submit an application to smpetfinder@gmail.com to get the process started.  Go to www.smallmiraclesrescue.org and click "How to Adopt".  There you will find the dog/puppy application available for download. The more information you provide, the faster the process is for all of us.  Once you are approved to adopt we will schedule an appointment to see the puppy in person and you will be allowed to take it home that day.  Due to the ease of our adoption process, please apply only if you are ready to adopt right now and committed to the level of care that having a puppy requires.  If you are not ready to adopt, we totally understand - just wait to apply until you are ready.  Many of our puppies are placed less than 72 hours after the application is submitted (ex: an application submitted on a Thurs could be approved and the puppy sent home as early as Saturday). 

Make sure to note in the email subject line which puppy you are interested in.  I will take back up applications for every puppy in the event an adoption falls through.

Adoption Fee Broken Down:

Before our puppies are available for adoption, they will always be spayed or neutered, vaccinated (distemper, bordatella, rabies if age appropriate), dewormed, and stool sample checked for parasites.  Adoption fee for our puppies is $325, an additional $30 for a microchip and registration and an additional small discounted amount for a 3 month supply of heartworm preventative, priced at $20.

It's no myth that the two of us are meant to be!  My name is Freyr and I am about to rule your world!  I am an 8 week old, 20lb., hound mix dude.  I will probably be medium to large when I am all done growing.  I have been so busy lately.  I am learning about house training, crate training, and how to "sit."  I have mastered the art of looking absolutely adorable at all times.  But I will need a really awesome human to love me forever and help guide me to be the best adult Freyr I can be! I get along with other dogs and cats.  I do need a 6ft privacy fence in my forever home (so no apartments for me).  I love to be with my humans and have fun!  I am all about the playtime life!  I need a super fun, active family to make some awesome memories with!  I will be ready to start our life of all good things on January 30th, so fill out my adoption application now!  


My adoption fee is $150 and includes 3 rounds of dewormer, 2 parvo/distemper vaccinations, Bordetella vaccination, spay/neuter, 2 wellness exams, and microchip! *adopters are responsible for final round of parvo/distemper vaccination and rabies vaccine if adopted before 12 weeks of age* If you are interested in adopting me/meeting me, please fill out an application at www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/

Age (best guess based on teeth): born in June 2017

Size (full grown best guess for puppies): 41lbs

Information: Dakota came to us with her puppies from a high kill shelter. She came in as a stray. She is shy at first but she does warm up and love on her humans. She does well with other dogs as long as they are not with her babies. Dakota is not sure what to think about some of the finer things in a dogs' life but she is getting used to them quickly and finding that belly rubs, pets, and soft beds are the way to go. Dakota has not had any accidents in the home. We are unsure how she does with a cat in the home as she only has been exposed to outdoor cats. 

 

We are a foster based rescue based out of Muskegon, MI. We have an application process for adopting our pets. We have an application on our website www.caninesrescue.com. PLEASE DO NOT EMAIL US WITH YOUR APPLICATION INFORMATION. WE REQUIRE YOU FILL OUT THE FORM. We check vet references, backgrounds for abuse or neglect and home ownership or speak to the landlord to verify you are allowed to have a pet. Once the application is received and approved then we will set up a time for you to come and meet our pups that are available. All our dogs are up to date on shots, microchipped, been dewormed at least once, and sterilized. All meet and greets are APPOINTMENT ONLY. We do not have a facility that the public can come and view our pets at.

animal.description:
Herman is a 1 year old, 50 lb Viszla mix. Herman is dog friendly boy that prefers to live in a cat free home. Herman does have hip dysplasia and has undergone FHO surgery and has recovered well. Viszla's are sleek dogs and due to the dysplasia he will need to keep his sleek physique. What a great boy!!

Despite the dysplasia Herman does enjoy running around and going for walks. This is not holding our boy back! We hope this doesn't keep you from adopting our handsome boy Herman. 

The adoption fee is $300 and covers age appropriate vaccines, a microchip, and a spay/neuter.

 Applications are typically worked in time stamp order based on date/time of submission. If you have other dogs in your home, they must all meet the potential adoptee. It may save you a trip to bring them with you when you visit, if you are certain you want to adopt a new family member. 

*****We are currently operating by appointment only during the social distancing stage of quarantine. If you want to meet this pet, or are interested in adopting, please submit an inquiry or email to email@townandcountryhumanesociety.org.

Someone from the rescue will contact you and/or your family and determine, on a broad level, whether you might be a fit for the animal. If so, they will provide instructions for completing the application. Your application will be reviewed and you will be contacted to set up a time to meet at the shelter or the foster home. The introduction between you and the pet will be supervised by one of the dog counselors or the foster. If all goes well, you can adopt during the same visit.

Please be sure to follow us on Facebook to learn more about Town and Country Humane Society and our mission.

animal.description:
If you love decadent, delicious, and delightful desserts, then MatchDog has your dish! Welcome the Cutie Pie Pups - chock full of fluffy morsels to tempt your sweet tooth! Indulge today!

Hello, my name is Flan! I am an incredibly handsome 2-year-old male French Poodle blend WEIGHING 9.9 POUNDS. I've had a bit of a rough start in life but, thankfully, was rescued by MatchDog. I'm ready to find my forever home! I have something called "Cherry Eye", a condition that can be corrected with surgery. Don't worry, though, because MDR is covering this cost. I couldn't be more grateful! You should know that I am crate trained and working hard on my house manners. While I may come across as shy at first, I LOVE to be around people, and I am great with other dogs and children. Humans generally describe me as calm and sweet - an all-around cuddle bug! In fact, once you get to know me, I promise Ill be your biggest F(L)AN:-) If you're looking for some sweet furry caramel custard, fill out an application for me, Flan, today!

If you think you are a perfect match for Flan please complete an application fully: https://www.petstablished.com/organization/243592

Flan has been fully vetted, is up to date on all vaccinations and on preventatives for heartworm, flea, and tick. We cannot guarantee breed information. You will find price guidelines for adoption at matchdogrescue.org and you can read about the whole adoption process and what MatchDog Rescue provides with each dog

This gorgeous MatchDog is currently being fostered and cared for at our own facility so as to look and feel his best when he meets you on Saturday February 13, 2021 . For the very best chance of securing a meet with this dog, you must be available all day on this date.

 

If you see a pending notification on this dog, it means we have informed the lucky family selected as the best match for this particular dog and they have agreed to come to the transport/event with the goal of taking the dog to their forever home. If for any reason this plan falls through, we will change the picture back to its original format and revisit other applications.

This dog recently arrived and is just settling in.  If you are interested in adopting, you MUST come in person during adoption hours and fill out an application.  Adoption hours and address are viewable on the website at www.smallmiraclesrescue.org


---FAQ---

Is This Dog Currently Available?... This dog is available at the Small Miracles rescue facility in Ellicott City.  To submit an application, please come meet this dog in person.  You can bring your application with you, or you can fill one out when you come in.  Dogs will be removed from PetFinder only when they have an approved application or more than three (3) interested applicants.

Where did this dog come from?...  We rescue dogs from 100% kill shelters in West Virginia and on occasion from Kentucky.  On rare occasions we accept owner surrenders.  Due to the nature of the shelters they were rescued from, we often do not know the dogs' history.

How Old is this dog?...  We look at a dogs' teeth to estimate its age, and then the age is reevaluated by our veterinary staff when the dog is spayed/neutered.  If an age is not posted online, please feel free to inquire.

Is this dog Good With Kids?...  We occasionally know for sure if a dog is good with kids because it came from a home with kids.  This is rare.  We always suggest you bring your children in to meet the dog if you are seriously interested in adopting.  Dogs may like some kids and may dislike others.  Dogs are individuals, just like kids are.

Is this dog Housebroken?...  Advice from a veterinarian:  Even if a dog is housebroken at my house, it does not mean that it understands not to pee at someone else's house.  It ONLY understands not to pee at my house.  Some dogs make the connection that they should only pee outside.  Some must be retrained when they come home.  All we can tell you for sure is whether/or not a dog's crate is clean when we come to walk them in the AM.  All this means is that they are crate trained and waited to pee until we took them outside.

What is this dog's Temperament?...  We do not have a clear picture of a dog's temperament until we have allowed them to settle in for a few days.  Even then they are living in a shelter environment with many other dogs and a lot of daily activity.  It can be difficult to say a dog is "calm" or "nervous" when the shelter environment is playing a big role in that behavior.  We only rescue FRIENDLY dogs who have no known bite history.  If a dog is at Small Miracles, it likes people and has a good temperament.  We always suggest you meet the dog to see if it is the right fit for your lifestyle. 

What are your Fees?...  Base adoption fee is $325 for adult dogs and puppies.  To this, we add a $30 microchip fee, which we register for you, and a 6 month supply of heartworm preventative.  Heartworm preventative costs $40-60 depending on the weight of the dog.  This means that a large dog will total $405.00 and an extra large dog will total $415.00.

Why can't I adopt a FREE dog?...  Our adoption fee covers many procedures which cost much more for us then the amount we ask for from you. We spay/neuter all pets, and we give them their first round of vaccines (canine distemper, bordatella, Rabies if age appropriate).  At a typical vet clinic this would cost you $500 at minimum for the surgery, and each vaccine is roughly $35 each.  Even if your adopted dog does not have all of its shots due to the mandatory waiting period between booster shots, we offer vaccinations at the low cost of $20/shot.  We test all dogs for heartworm disease and tickborn illnesses such as Lymes.  We never euthanize a heartworm positive dog, and treatment routinely costs us $3000/dog.  We collect a fecal sample from every rescued dog and run a microscopic parasite test.  Any parasites found will be treated with two rounds of the appropriate dewormer.  We treat all dogs for fleas and ticks with Advantage.  If a dog has significant dental disease or "very dirty teeth", we will perform a dental cleaning when the dog has its spay/neuter surgery.  A dental cleaning with extractions would cost you upwards of $400-600 at your local vet clinic.

ALSO NOTE... Small Miracle is a 501(c)(3) charitable organization.  We survive off of our adoption fees and donations from the community.  We are a non-profit animal rescue and do not receive income from tax revenue as some county shelters do. 

For more information including Adoption Hours and Rescue Address, please visit our website at www.smallmiraclesrescue.org
